      "primitive_binding_source": "",
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "Temporal Event-Stream Concordance Index. Takes two sparse event-location sequences on a shared one-dimensional timeline and performs tolerance-based correspondence within a fixed temporal radius. Events are counted as concordant when a counterpart exists within the search window, then converted into a scalar agreement score using a mode-selected normalization rule that accounts for overlap versus disagreement. The result is a bounded similarity measure of detection consistency under temporal uncertainty.. Applications: Comparing spike-event annotations from two neural signal processing pipelines in electrophysiology., Quantifying agreement between independent seismic phase pickers on earthquake waveform timelines., Measuring concordance of transient-event detectors in astrophysical time-series surveys., Evaluating consistency between two fault-trigger logs in industrial condition-monitoring systems.",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
